Create a new branch:

git branch <branch_name>
Switch to a branch:

git checkout <branch_name>
Alternatively, with Git version 2.23 and later:

git switch <branch_name>
Create and switch to a new branch:

git checkout -b <new_branch_name>
or

git switch -c <new_branch_name>
List all branches:

git branch
Delete a local branch:

git branch -d <branch_name>
Force delete a local branch:

git branch -D <branch_name>
Push a branch to the remote repository:

git push origin <branch_name>
Fetch the latest changes from a remote repository:

git fetch
Merge changes from one branch to another:

git checkout <destination_branch>
git merge <source_branch>
or

git merge --no-ff <source_branch>
Rebase changes onto another branch:

git checkout <source_branch>
git rebase <destination_branch>
View the commit history of a branch:

git log
View a graphical representation of the commit history:

git log --graph --oneline --all
Resolve merge conflicts:
After resolving conflicts, you can use:

git add <conflicted_file>
git rebase --continue
Show changes between branches:

git diff <branch1>..<branch2>
Rename a branch:

git branch -m <old_branch_name> <new_branch_name>
Undo local changes in a branch:

git checkout -- <file_name>
Undo local commits (soft reset):

git reset --soft HEAD^
Undo local commits (hard reset):

git reset --hard HEAD^

git push origin <branch_name>
